README

Author: Guan Gui, Han Gao
Simple Shell 

This is a simple shell written in C language. Created by Guan Gui, and Han Gao, as operating system course project. We satisfied the minimum requirement and finish extra requirments.

Features:
•	We implement the basic build in commands such as cd exit, quit, print, echo. Thus we can use cd to change directory. Besides, we can use ~ symbol in the directory path to represent home directory.
•	Background operations.  Example ls –l | wc &
•	Redirection.  Such as wc < invalid.file or wc < valid.file
•	Directory display.
•	Environment variables setting.
•	Background Process Tracking.
